# Smoke-test crontab: write an identity marker to /var/tmp/cron-marker every
# second so the test can poll for it quickly and confirm the cron role is
# running and executing jobs as the expected app user.
#
# This uses supercronic's extended 7-field syntax (a leading seconds field),
# which the image documents as a feature -- so the test also exercises that
# grammar, not just classic 5-field cron. A per-minute '* * * * *' job would
# only first fire on the next minute boundary, forcing a ~60s+ poll window.
#
# NB: the seconds field needs the FULL 7-field form. A 6-field line is parsed
# by supercronic's cronexpr as 'minute hour dom month dow year' (year is the
# other optional field), NOT as a leading seconds field -- so it silently stays
# per-minute. Seven fields disambiguate it to a true per-second schedule.
#
#   field: second minute hour day-of-month month day-of-week year  command
* * * * * * * /bin/sh -c 'echo "cron-ok-$(id -un)" > /var/tmp/cron-marker'
